items.name: IMU_ROS2_CMP10A
items.description: The nine-axis ARHS attitude sensor MEMS magnetometer bought from yahboom performs well in ROS1, but when it is used in ROS2, the data of a number of sensors will tend to zero indefinitely and the data will float in chaos. The warehouse has rewritten the driver code of the IMU CMP10A. So that it can read the data correctly in ROS2 HUMBLE.
